{
  "stem": "1965.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 363.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I wanted to live more than ever, especially because Madame Rothschild was such a darling woman, and always so caring for all of us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so that experience led us to more hiding places.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we ended up in a place known as Auderghem.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Auderghem is where I stayed till the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it is over there that we had a little bit-- this was the year, the latter part of '44, the early part of '45.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I know that because both Sam and Jack told me that we came together when it was very warm.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we all presume that it was the summer time, sometimes in July, that we got together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I keep saying no, it had to be May.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they keep saying it was so warm that we couldn't even put on a jacket.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So in Belgium when it's hot, it's 75 degrees.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] It's not like Miami.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in those days, in-- in the Belgian climate, you have a lot-- a lot of rain, which penetrates right through your bones, and-- and snow sometimes in certain parts, especially the [NON-ENGLISH] area, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But you don't have very much of a dry, sunny day, except for sometimes in the two months July, and August.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In Auderghem I found more peace.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I became even more attached to Madame Rothschild.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And her husband, who was never in vision during all this time that we were hiding and running, finally came to Auderghem.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she reunited with her husband.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he was such a wonderful person.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there I remember I would peel potatoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I will clean green beans.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was a luxury, to clean potatoes, to clean green beans, because remember, before I always was eating turnips.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
